Jerome C. Daniel Overlook Above the Hollywood Bowl
Descrip: The Jerome C. Daniel Overlook above the Hollywood Bowl is one of the most visited sites along scenic Mulholland Drive in the Hollywood Hills. The scenic overlook provides views of the Hollywood Bowl, the Cahuenga Pass, Downtown Los Angeles, the Santa Monica Mountains, Griffith Observatory and the Hollywood Sign. On a clear day, one can see the Pacific Ocean and Catalina Island. Interpretive panels and viewing platforms augment the vistor experience.  A small parking lot accomodates cars for a short visit.
